Class Algorithms

  • java.lang.Object
    • ms.ipp.Algorithms

  • public class Algorithms
extends java.lang.Object
    A collection of routines that manipulate Java class related to functional programming, such as Function, Predicate, Operator, Consumer, Supplier, etc.

        @SafeVarargs
public static <T,U> java.util.function.BiPredicate<T,U> and(java.util.function.BiPredicate<? super T,? super U>... preds)
        Creates a new BiPredicate which returns true if and only if all given BiPredicates return true. Is equivalent to: 
         accumulateNonNulls(BiPredicate::and, predicates);
        Parameters:
        preds - a parameter array of BiPredicates. Nulls in the array are ignored
        Returns:
        null if all predicates are null or a concatenated BiPredicate otherwise.
        See Also:
        accumulateNonNulls(BiFunction, Object...)

      • accumulateNonNulls

        public static <T,U> U accumulateNonNulls(java.util.function.BiFunction<U,T,U> accumulator,
                                         T... elems)
        Reduces all non-null elements to a single element by means of a given accumulator.
        The documented usage is to join multiple Consumers or BiConsumers.
        Parameters:
        accumulator -
        elems - the elements to join together, null are ignored.
        Returns:
        null if all elements are null or the first non-null element if it is the only one in the array. Otherwise, the result of the last call to accumulator.
        See Also:
        Stream.reduce(BinaryOperator)
